newsitem.title: USA: Newark, N.J. $39 mln reoffered at 5.35 pct in 2011.
newsitem.headline: Newark, N.J. $39 mln reoffered at 5.35 pct in 2011.

text.p: Morgan Stanley & Co said Tuesday it won $39.4 million Newark, N.J., improvement bonds, reoffering the bonds at a top yield of 5.35 percent in 2011.
A bid by Merrill Lynch was reported as the winner, but was rejected because it was late, market sources said.
